------------------------NEXUS AND MAVEN INTEGRATION
Open your pom.xml file:

Inside the <distributionManagement> section, add the configuration for deploying to Nexus. Replace the placeholders with your actual Nexus repository details.

Insert the <distributionManagement> section immediately after the opening <project> tag.

<distributionManagement>
    <repository>
        <id>nexus</id>
        <url>http://40.76.109.117:8081/repository/myapp-release/</url>
    </repository>
    <snapshotRepository>
        <id>nexus</id>
        <url>http://40.76.109.117:8081/repository/myapp-snapshot/</url>
    </snapshotRepository>
</distributionManagement>


http://40.76.109.117:8081/repository/myapp-snapshot/

http://40.76.109.117:8081/repository/myapp-release/


adding the <server> configuration in your settings.xml file (usually located in your .m2 directory under your user's home directory)

vi ~/.m2/settings.xml

<settings>
    <!-- Other configuration elements -->

    <servers>
        <server>
            <id>nexus</id>
            <username>admin</username>
            <password>password</password>
        </server>
    </servers>

    <!-- Other configuration elements -->
</settings>


mvn clean package install deploy
